                         <script>
                          ;(function() {

	

  // NYT app detection code
  var isInApp = !!(
    // sometimes this query param is present
    window.location.search.indexOf('nytapp') > -1 ||
    // usually the user agent is set
    window.navigator.userAgent.match(/nyt[-_]?(?:ios|android)/i) ||
    // on hybrid articles in android, the user agent and qs is missing
    (window.navigator.userAgent.match(/android/i) && window.__HYBRID__)
  );

  var isInAppHome = document.querySelector('.nytapp-home-interactive') !== null;
  var isAndroid = window.navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Android') > -1;
  var isIos = !!window.navigator.userAgent.match(/iP(hone|ad)/i);

  if (isInApp && isAndroid) document.querySelector('html').classList.add('nytapp-android');
  if (isInApp && isIos) document.querySelector('html').classList.add('nytapp-ios');

  // NYT apps resize function
  // Resizes the interactive webview height after a 1 second pause
  if (!document.querySelector("#programming-list")) {
    if ( window.NYTG && window.NYTG.enqueue) {
      setTimeout(function() {
        var container = document.querySelector("#g-hp-tabs");
        var windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
        function resize() {
          var height = container.offsetHeight;
          window.NYTG.enqueue(
            JSON.stringify({ id: 0, type: 'resize', options: { height: height } })
            )
        }
        window.addEventListener("resize", function() {
          if ( window.innerWidth != windowWidth ) {
            windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
            resize();
          }
        });
        resize();
      }, 1000);
    }
  }


  var tabPromo = document.getElementById('g-hp-tabs')
  var tabs = tabPromo.querySelectorAll('.g-hp-tab')
  var buttons = tabPromo.querySelectorAll('.g-hp-tab-btn')

  for (var i = buttons.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
  	buttons[i].addEventListener('click', function(e){
  		for (var j = buttons.length - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
  			buttons[j].classList.remove('g-active')
  		}
  		var slug = this.getAttribute('data-tab')
  		this.classList.add('g-active')

  		for (var j = tabs.length - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
  			if(tabs[j].getAttribute('data-tab') === slug) {
  				tabs[j].classList.add('g-active')
  			} else {
  				tabs[j].classList.remove('g-active')
  			}
  		}
  		
  	}, false)
  }
})();
                         </script>
                         <script type="text/javascript">
                          ;(function() {
		var images = document.querySelectorAll('#g-hp-tabs .g-tab-fader .g-photo-wrap'),
			counter = 0;

		var hasCaptions = false;
		var speed = hasCaptions ? 7500 : 5000

		var prev = counter

		if (images[counter]) images[counter].classList.add('g-photo-active')

		setInterval(function(){
			
			prev = counter
			counter++
			if(counter > images.length-1) counter = 0
			if (images[counter]) images[counter].classList.add('g-photo-active')
			// console.log(prev, counter)
			setTimeout(function(){
				// console.log(prev, counter)
				if (images[prev]) images[prev].classList.remove('g-photo-active')
			}, 175)
		}, speed)
	})()
                         </script>

                         <script>
                          ;(function() {

  var tabPromo = document.getElementById('g-hp-tabs')
  var video = tabPromo.querySelector('#g-vhs-video')

  if(video){

  		// console.log(video.offsetWidth)
	  	var wrap = video.querySelector('#g-vhs-video-wrap')
	  	

		const player = VHS.video({
			id: video.getAttribute('data-id'),
			container: wrap,
			headline: video.getAttribute('data-hed'),
			live: video.getAttribute('data-live'),
			autoplay: video.getAttribute('data-autoplay') === 'true',
			posterUrl: video.getAttribute('data-poster'),
			// posterUrl: 'https://static01.nyt.com/images/2020/06/15/autossell/Covid-Funeral-Home-onsiteC/Covid-Funeral-Home-onsiteC-videoLarge.jpg',
			ratio: '16:9',
			controls: true,
			loop: true,
			muted: true,
			cover: video.getAttribute('data-autoplay') !== 'true',
			ads: false,
			width: '100%',
		    height: '100%'
		    // width: tabPromo.offsetWidth,
		    // height: tabPromo.offsetWidth * 0.66666666666
		});

		if(isInAppHome || isAndroid || isIos){
			document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() {
			  if (document.visibilityState === "hidden") {
			    player.pause()
			  } else {
			  	player.play()
			  }
			})
		}
	}
})();

                   <script>
                    (function() {
    window.NYTG = window.NYTG || {};
    window.NYTG.VIRUS_ASSETS = "https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/608210720c4939d1780e60bf24790ee365d7b315/".slice(0, -1);
    window.NYTG.VIRUS_BIG_ASSETS = "https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/assets/".slice(0, -1);

    var supports_import = false;
    var can_use_import = location.hostname.indexOf('preview.n' + 'yt.net') == -1;
    var shimport_url = window.NYTG.VIRUS_ASSETS + "/shimport@1.0.1.js";
    var shimport_promise;

    try {
      new Function("if(0)import('')")();
      supports_import = true;
    } catch(e) { }

    if (!can_use_import || !supports_import) {
      shimport_promise = new Promise(function(fulfil, reject) {
        var s = document.createElement("script");
        s.src = shimport_url;
        s.onload = function() {
          fulfil(__shimport__);
        };
        s.onerror = reject;

        document.head.appendChild(s);
      });
    }

    window.NYTG.load = function(module) {
      var url = new URL(module, location.href).href;

      if (can_use_import && supports_import) {
        return eval("import('" + url + "')");
      } else {
        return shimport_promise.then(function(shimport) {
          return shimport.load(url);
        });
      }
    };

    // for --live
    window.NYTG.subscribers = {};
    window.NYTG.watch = function(url, cb) {
      if (!window.NYTG.subscribers[url]) window.NYTG.subscribers[url] = [];
      window.NYTG.subscribers[url].push(cb);
      window.NYTG.load(url).then(cb);
    };

    var cache = new Map();
    window.NYTG.fetch = url => {
      if (!cache.has(url)) {
        cache.set(url, fetch(url).then(r => r.json().catch(err => {
          cache.delete(url);
          throw err;
        })));
      }
      return cache.get(url);
    }
  }());
                   </script>

    var templateStyle  = "template-option-" + ("" || "black-icons");
    // Check for dark mode flag
    var isDarkMode     = "".match(/y|yes|true/) !== null;

                      Promise.all([
							NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/608210720c4939d1780e60bf24790ee365d7b315/data/timeseries/en/USA-only.json"), NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/608210720c4939d1780e60bf24790ee365d7b315/data/timeseries/en/NYT-World-only.json"), NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/608210720c4939d1780e60bf24790ee365d7b315/data/timeseries/en/CAN.json"), NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/608210720c4939d1780e60bf24790ee365d7b315/data/us_counties.json"), NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/608210720c4939d1780e60bf24790ee365d7b315/data/vaccine_summary.json")
						]).then(function(data) {
							var target = document.querySelector('[data-component="cv1"]');
							var url = NYTG.VIRUS_ASSETS + '/build/js/dashboard.js';
							var props = { timeseries: data[0], timeseriesWorld: data[1], timeseriesCanada: data[2], counties: data[3], vaccine_summary: data[4], average_change_cases_two_weeks: "-21", average_change_deaths_two_weeks: "-17", average_change_cases_two_weeks_world: "2", average_change_deaths_two_weeks_world: "-21", average_change_cases_two_weeks_can: "9", average_change_deaths_two_weeks_can: "-38", us_maps: ["usa_map","vaccine_distribution"], int_maps: ["world_map","vaccine_map","usa_map"], show_county: true, type: "spotlight" }

							
							let component;

							NYTG.load(url).then((mod) => {
								const Component = mod.default;

								component = new Component({
									target,
									hydrate: true,
									props
								});
							});
						
						});
                     </script>

                   <script>
                    ;(function() {
  // NYT apps resize function
  // Resizes the interactive webview height after a 1 second pause
  // Don't run resizer if it's in a programming list webview
  if ( window.NYTG && window.NYTG.enqueue && !document.querySelector("#programming-list") ) {
    setTimeout(function() {
      var container = document.querySelector("#g-2020-03-16-coronavirus-maps-embed");
      var windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
      function resize() {
        var height = container.offsetHeight;
        window.NYTG.enqueue(
          JSON.stringify({ id: 0, type: 'resize', options: { height: height } })
        )
      }
      window.addEventListener("resize", function() {
        if ( window.innerWidth != windowWidth ) {
          windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
          resize();
        }
      });
      resize();
    }, 1000);
  }

})();
                   </script>

                          <script type="text/javascript">
                           ;(function() {

    clearInterval(window.hpFaderTimer_homepage);

    var images = document.querySelectorAll('#homepage-home-fader.g-home-fader .g-home-fader-photo-wrap'),
      counter = 0;

    var hasCaptions = true;
    var speed = hasCaptions ? 7500 : 5000

    window.hpFaderTimer_homepage = setInterval(function() {
      var prev = counter;
      counter++;
      if(counter >  images.length-1) counter = 0
        images[counter].classList.add('g-home-fader-photo-active');
        // console.log(prev, counter)

        setTimeout(function(){
          // console.log(prev, counter)
         images[prev].classList.remove('g-home-fader-photo-active');
        }, 250)
    },  speed);

    // NYT app detection code
    var isInApp = !!(
      // sometimes this query param is present
      window.location.search.indexOf('nytapp') > -1 ||
      // usually the user agent is set
      window.navigator.userAgent.match(/nyt[-_]?(?:ios|android)/i) ||
      // on hybrid articles in android, the user agent and qs is missing
      (window.navigator.userAgent.match(/android/i) && window.__HYBRID__)
    );

    var isInAppHome = document.querySelector('.nytapp-home-interactive') !== null;
    var isAndroid = window.navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Android') > -1;
    var isIos = !!window.navigator.userAgent.match(/iP(hone|ad)/i);

    if (isInApp && isAndroid) document.querySelector('html').classList.add('nytapp-android');
    if (isInApp && isIos) document.querySelector('html').classList.add('nytapp-ios');

    // don't resize if inside of programming list
    if (!document.querySelector("#programming-list")) {
    // NYT apps resize function
    // Resizes the interactive webview height after a 1 second pause
      if ( window.NYTG && window.NYTG.enqueue) {
        setTimeout(function() {
          var container = document.querySelector("#homepage-home-fader.g-home-fader");
          var windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
          function resize() {
            var height = container.offsetHeight;
            window.NYTG.enqueue(
              JSON.stringify({ id: 0, type: 'resize', options: { height: height } })
              )
          }
          window.addEventListener("resize", function() {
            if ( window.innerWidth != windowWidth ) {
              windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
              resize();
            }
          });
          resize();
        }, 1000);
      }
    }

  })();
                          </script>
                         </div>
                        </section>

                    </div>

                    <div class="css-k008qs">
                     <div class="css-r3xxt2 e5w41om0" span="4">
                      <div class="css-8gwzkc e5w41om1">
                       <section class="story-wrapper">
                        <a class="css-kej3w4" data-story="nyt://article/d31e02dc-989c-5929-9595-39974ac50682" data-uri="nyt://article/d31e02dc-989c-5929-9595-39974ac50682" data-visited="" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/02/magazine/he-was-the-hero-of-hotel-rwanda-now-hes-accused-of-terrorism.html">
                         <h3 class="css-3gcxf0 e1lsht870" size="200">
                          <span>
                           He Was the Hero of Hotel Rwanda. Now Hes Accused of Terrorism.
                          </span>
                         </h3>
                        </a>
                        <div class="css-1a00rns e16ry1jj0" color="orange">
                        </div>
                        <a class="css-kej3w4" data-story="nyt://article/d31e02dc-989c-5929-9595-39974ac50682" data-uri="nyt://article/d31e02dc-989c-5929-9595-39974ac50682" data-visited="" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/02/magazine/he-was-the-hero-of-hotel-rwanda-now-hes-accused-of-terrorism.html">
                         <p class="css-oemrl2">
                          Long hailed for his bravery during the 1994 Rwandan genocide, Paul Rusesabagina is now charged with being an insurgent leader. Did Rwanda change, or did he?
                         </p>
                        </a>
                       </section>
                      </div>
                     </div>
                     <div class="css-1bs4uk3 e5w41om0" span="6">
                      <div class="css-1rvhhh9 e5w41om1">
                       <div>
                        <a class="css-kej3w4" data-uri="nyt://article/d31e02dc-989c-5929-9595-39974ac50682" data-visited="" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/02/magazine/he-was-the-hero-of-hotel-rwanda-now-hes-accused-of-terrorism.html">
                         <picture class="css-cov0u6">

                          <img alt="Paul Rusesabagina in 2005. He sheltered some 1,300 people at a hotel while violence convulsed Rwanda." class="css-hdqqnp" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2021/03/07/magazine/07mag-rwanda-01/07mag-rwanda-01-threeByTwoSmallAt2X-v2.jpg?format=pjpg&amp;quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale"/>
                         </picture>
                        </a>
                       </div>

     </div>
    </main>

(isDarkMode) ? \" \" + \"template-mode-dark\" : \"\";\n    \u002F\u002F Check for feature style flag\n    var isFeatureStyle = \"\".toLowerCase().match(\u002Ffeature|featured|feat\u002F) !== null;\n    var featureStyle   = (isFeatureStyle) ? \"template-style-feature\" : \"template-style-standard\";\n    \u002F\u002F Set classes on body element\n    var tBody          = document.body.classList.add(...[templateType.trim(), templateStyle.trim(),\n      darkMode.trim(), featureStyle.trim()].filter(d =\u003E !!d));\n  })();\n\u003C\u002Fscript\u003E\n\n\n\u003C!-- story
